sentences: François Benoist (10 September 1794 – 6 May 1878) was a French organist, composer, and pedagogue.
He studied music at the Conservatoire de Paris and won the Prix de Rome in 1815 for his cantata Œnone.
In 1819, he became organist (organiste du roi) and professor of organ at the Conservatoire; he held the latter post for half a century.
